cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.SI 

This paper is about malware detection using machine learning techniques on behavioral analysis reports. It falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with detecting and attributing threats. The paper also extensively uses natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a framework for automated feature engineering, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on various datasets, which falls under the category of systems and information theory (cs.SI).
